{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/confessions-of-an-automation-addict-javaone/","result":{"data":{"post":{"id":"705ddbab-ddef-5838-a57e-bc28dcfed02d","html":"<p>I’ve never seen a job I didn’t want to automate. Sometimes it’s worked out well, sometimes automation has turned a small nuisance into a big, fragile, free-time-eating monster nuisance. In this talk, I’ll explore why we automate, when to automate, the hazards of automation and the – big – rewards of automation. I’m part of the team developing IBM’s WebSphere Liberty application server. We’ve used a mix of off-the-shelf and home-rolled tools and processes to work smarter and more productively. I’ll describe what we’ve learned as WebSphere has transitioned to DevOps and continuous delivery and why I still can’t resist trying to automate all the things.\nThese are slides from a 2014 presentation at GeekOut UK.</p>","excerpt":"I’ve never seen a job I didn’t want to automate. Sometimes it’s worked out well, sometimes automation has turned a small nuisance into a big…","fields":{"title":"Confessions of an Automation Addict","slug":"/confessions-of-an-automation-addict-javaone/","prefix":"2015-10-25","shortDate":"10-25","category":"devops","author":"Holly Cummins","displayCategory":"devops","geography":{"flag":"","country":"United States"},"video":{"title":null,"html":null,"url":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oQqe2BpEfY8"},"slides":{"title":"Confessions of an Automation Addict","html":"<p data-notist=\"holly-cummins/r76rQx\">View <a href=\"https://noti.st/holly-cummins/r76rQx\">Confessions of an Automation Addict</a> on Notist.</p><script async src=\"https://on.notist.cloud/embed/002.js\"></script>","url":"https://noti.st/holly-cummins/r76rQx/confessions-of-an-automation-addict"},"oembeds":null,"cover":{"childImageSharp":{"resize":{"src":"/static/0aecf99963d1f3a453aab38d7306374b/9dc27/audience.jpg"}}}},"frontmatter":{"type":"talk","event":"JavaOne","keynote":null,"code":n